<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-12-27T10:24:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-12-27T10:24:00-05:00" n="798" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d798">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/7878: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Commissioner at Riga</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Young</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Riga</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-12-27T17:00:00+01:36"><hi rend="italic">December
                                            27, 1920—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 5:21
                                    p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>284. Situation apparently becoming more grave and in view large Red
                                Cross personnel and difficulty attending evacuation should that
                                become necessary I request immediate despatch of nearest American
                                naval vessel. There are controlling reasons why despatch of vessel
                                should not be given publicity. See Hollyday’s 144.<note n="54" xml:id="d798fn54">Not printed.</note></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Young</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>